.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "28 September - 05 October 2025" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell - A simple shell implementation

.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a basic command-line interpreter that allows users to execute commands 
and interact with the operating system. 
It provides a straightforward interface for executing commands and managing processes.

.SH OPTIONS
There are no command-line options for simple_shell.

.SH COMMANDS
simple_shell supports the following:

.IP "command [arguments]" 4
Executes the specified command with the given arguments.

.IP "exit" 4
Exit the shell.

.IP "env" 4
Display the current environment variables.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The simple_shell program returns the following exit status values:

.IP "0" 4
Indicates successful execution.

.IP "1" 4
Indicates that an error occurred during command execution.

.SH EXAMPLES
To execute a command, type the command followed by any necessary arguments:

.IP "#cisfun$ /bin/ls -l" 4
Runs the \fBls\fR command with the \fB-l\fR option.

.IP "#cisfun$ echo Hello World" 4
Prints "Hello World" to the standard output.

.SH SEE ALSO
bash(1), sh(1)

.SH AUTHORS
Mahammad Atlukhanov, Amin Baghiyev
